 this exact manner=2E  Doesn't seem likely though=2E  

It always bothers me that alot of these card systems do not keep=
 track of access=2E  If they kept track of when the card was used,=
 how often and other statistics, it would be possible to catch=
 someone trying to subvert the system in this manner=2E

It is more likely that stuff is walking out the door at the end=
 of a shift=2E  With high tech crime it is often the lowest tech=
 answer=2E

"Scrap unzipped his gym bag and placed the box on Jon's desk=2E"

The human being is always either the weakest link or the greatest=
 strength=2E  It all depends on your perspective or who's=
 watching=2E

Giving "Bernice Clueless" the benefit of the doubt she may have=
 thought initially that she left it at home or lost it somewhere=
 that she might be able to find it and not wanted to risk the=
 wrath of the bosses by bringing attention to the fact that she=
 had lost it if infact she could find it in the first twenty four=
 hours=2E  Never underestimate the human factor of not wanting to=
 be blamend=2E  People often talk themselves into stupid things in=
 order to avoid being blamed=2E

It is difficult to put cameras everywhere but if he had secured=
 storage areas you would think that he could have covered the=
 access points to this secured storage with minimal cameras at=
 all entrances=2E Of course then he has to count on humans again to=
 change recording media=2E

Good Story=2E Hope to hear more soon=2E


			</div>
		</div><div class="blogs_commententry">
